WU T ie-fengZHU Xiao-ning
（School of T raffic and T ransportationBeijing Jiaotong U niversityBeijing 100044China）

Abstract：T he container throughput in Chinese ports has kept the first position for 7years in the world since2003w hile the level of development of intermodal sea-rail transportation is extremely inconsistent with its international status．Based on thisaiming at the deficiencies of development of intermodal sea-rail transportation in Chinese portsthe existing three types of intermodal searail transportation operating mode are analyzed deeply from perspectives of their advantagesdisadvantages and respective influencing factors in this paperw hich stands at the conflicting point of view between transportation volume and transportation capacity．T henthe paper gives the problem solution program w hich constraint the development of intermodal sea-rail transportationsuch as institution constructionrailway network layoutsmarket and serviceskey technologiesetc． Key words：container；intermodal sea-rail transportation；development；program

